# Coding Agent Workflow

Follow the shared workflow rules in @CLAUDE.md. This rule ensures Cursor loads project-specific config and the session checklist even when Claude `@` imports are unavailable.

## Session Start Checklist

1. Read `tasks/memory.md` for persistent patterns and lessons
2. Check `tasks/todo.md` for in-progress work
3. Check `tasks/lessons.md` for self-improvement notes
4. Run `/memory-maintain` (self-gates — only does work every 5 sessions or when overdue)

## Harness Notes (Cursor)

- **Skills**: `.agents/skills/` (canonical) — invoke with `/skill-name`
- **Subagents**: `.cursor/agents/` — delegate via the Task tool
- **Hooks**: `.cursor/hooks.json` — sessionStart/stop orientation
- **Project rules**: see @.cursor/rules/project-config.mdc (content from `.claude/project.md`)

## Workflow Summary

PRD (greenfield) → `/plan` (spec + tasks) → user confirms → `/build` (autonomous TDD) → `/quality-gate` → `/wrap-up-session`

Hard gate: no source code changes without a plan in `tasks/todo.md` and user confirmation.
